You can see an animal in your house if you Google search an animal name (on iPhone or android) and then press ‘View in 3D’. It opens your camera and soon will show you the animal moving in your room. You can walk around it and take a picture of it with people.
Search for :
Lion
Tiger
Cheetah
Shark
Hedgehog
Duck
Emperor penguin
Wolf
Angler fish
Goat
Rottweiler
Snakes
Eagle
Brown bear
Alligator
Horse
Shetland pony
Macaw
Pug
Turtle
Cat
Octopus
Dog
Then check out the fun facts listed about each one!

post_text: Are you done with your library books already? We will have a cart full of books available for check out STARTING THIS FRIDAY and then the following WEDNESDAYS AND FRIDAYS at the grab and go lunch stations in Maitland, Graham, and Skidmore. For everyone's safety, we will not be allowing anyone into the actual libraries, but we will do our best to provide a large selection for all ages in each town. If you'd like to see a certain kind of book, leave me a comment under this post. If you want a specific book reserved for you, an online Google request form is available. And please... remember to return books before you take more. :) Happy reading! (Feel free to share this post to spread the word!)

post_text: As I get older, my favorite part about Christmas and birthdays is seeing the excitement in my child’s eyes when he opens his presents.
